.TH "port_chk" 9 "port_chk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
port_chk \- check port register bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" port_chk
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "int offset "  ","
.BI "u16 bits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "port" 12
The port index.
.IP "offset" 12
The offset of the port register.
.IP "bits" 12
The data bits to check.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks whether the specified bits of the port register are set
or not.

Return 0 if the bits are not set.
